OL,3,CSouth Scotland: The race for a place
OL,4,Con the regional list
OL,6,FPrior to that the town had been in
OL,7,Feconomic decline and many locals had
OL,8,Fbeen forced to move away to find work.
OL,10,FAnne Barclay grew up in the town and
OL,11,Fis now the communities director for
OL,12,Fthe Wigtown Festival Company.
OL,14,FAnne said: "I was still at the local
OL,15,Fprimary school when we became book
OL,16,Ftown but at that time it was almost
OL,17,Flike you could see the tumble weed
OL,18,Frolling down the street.
OL,26,@vD@LOU
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G7/19
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,353,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F352A1777554668
OL,3,CSouth Scotland: The race for a place
OL,4,Con the regional list
OL,6,F"It's made a phenomenal difference,
OL,7,Fpeople choosing to move to live here,
OL,8,Fto invest in our community."
OL,10,FWigtown is quite remote and, despite
OL,11,Fits success, people living there still
OL,12,Fface some challenges.
OL,14,FAnne explained some of the issues:
OL,15,F"The need to reinvigorate the town
OL,16,Fcentre, the need for more affordable
OL,17,Fhomes so that families and young
OL,18,Fpeople can stay here, sustainable
OL,19,Ftransport and improved local transport
OL,20,Flinks."
OL,26,@pD@\O]wD@AOU|D@GO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G8/19
